CatDescriptText: Jacqueline Terry, Waitress-cook, Uptown 88 Bar, 2335-1/2 LaPlace Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1958, pg. 6 with question: "Do you believe the trouble in Middle East will start an atomic world war?" answer reads: "Yes, I do. Sending troops into the Middle East looks like the United States is trying to interfere.  Those people, over there, want to run their own affairs."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Jacqueline Terry wearing light colored short sleeve shirt with pen in left breast pocket, apron, and wristwatch on left wrist, seated at booth with table and ashtray on left in interior with two toned walls, possibly Uptown 88 Bar
